benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Add custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC10, @TC12, @TC14, @TC15, @TC18, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC24, @TC25 ensure successful creation with valid data and headers.
Empty Response: @TC10 covers adding an empty array, expecting an empty response.
Invalid Payload: @TC08, @TC09, @TC21 cover malformed request bodies, missing bodies, and invalid JSON.
Non-Existent Invoice Item: @TC05, @TC23 cover attempts with non-existent IDs.
Invalid ID Format: @TC06 covers invalid UUID formats.
Authorization: @TC07, @TC12 cover missing or invalid authentication headers.
System Errors: @TC13 covers service unavailability scenarios.
Large Payloads: @TC14 tests maximum allowed number of custom fields.
Response Time: @TC15 tests response within acceptable threshold.
Regression: @TC17 tests duplicate custom field names handling.
Persistence & Retrieval: @TC18 verifies custom fields are stored and retrievable.
Edge Cases: @TC19, @TC20, @TC21 test maximum/minimum lengths, special characters, and injection attempts.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under high request rates.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Retry Logic: No explicit tests for transient network failures beyond simple retries.
Partial Updates & PATCH: No scenarios testing partial modifications or PATCH-specific behaviors.
Soft Deletes & Concurrency: No tests for soft delete behavior or race conditions during updates.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to ensure proper handling of large datasets.
Include scenarios for rate limiting and throttling to verify system stability under load.
Implement tests to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Create explicit retry logic tests for transient network failures.
Add PATCH method tests for partial updates and concurrency control.
Include tests for soft delete behaviors and race conditions during concurrent modifications.
